


What is the definition of an API?
Application Programming Interface
When you use an application on your mobile phone, the application connects to the Internet and sends data to a server. The server then retrieves that data, interprets it, performs the necessary actions and sends it back to your phone

What is the primary purpose in Web based applications?
They work as the middle man, allowing developers to build new programmatic interactions between the various applications people and businesses use on a daily basis.
A web-based application is any application that uses a website as the interface or front-end. Users can easily access the application from any computer connected to the Internet using a standard browser.
